This utility locates and extracts all of the GRIB2 messages from within a
specified input file, writing each into its own separate output file with
a unique filename.

Example:

	xg2mg [options] <inputfile>

will extract all of the GRIB2 messages from <inputfile> into the following
filenames:

	xg2mg.out.(pid).000001
	xg2mg.out.(pid).000002
	xg2mg.out.(pid).000003
	.
	.
	xg2mg.out.(pid).(last#)

where:
	(pid) = pid of xg2mg process
	(last#) = total number of GRIB2 messages in file

and possible options are:

	-v	prints version information and exits
	-g	retains any GTS bulletin information associated with the
		GRIB2 message in each output file
